[2026-03-13T17:24:09Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01A1Ma3kLe2eZceEu6Ga6SRP","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Let me compile all my findings into a comprehensive report:\n\n## Web UI Code Analysis - Complete Report\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's a comprehensive understanding of the web UI related code:\n\n### 1. **Handler That Serves Step Content**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n**Main Handler:** `handleAPIStepContent` (lines 1413-1495)\n- **Endpoint:** `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n- **Purpose:** Returns the content (prompt, script, command, or workflow reference) for a step when clicked in the project detail view\n- **Key Logic:**\n  - Resolves the project directory\n  - Looks up the workflow (checks container workflows first, then host workflows)\n  - Finds the specific step in the workflow\n  - Reads the step's content from referenced files using the `file()` DSL syntax\n  - Supports multiple content types: `prompt`, `command`, `script`, `run`, `workflow_name`\n  - Returns text/plain response\n\n**Helper Functions:**\n- `resolveFileRef()` - Resolves `file(\"path\")` syntax to actual file contents\n- `readScriptFromCommand()` - Extracts script file paths from run commands and reads them\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Step Content Rendering in the UI**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 408-441)\n\n**JavaScript Function:** `openDrawer(workflowName, stepName)`\n- Handles click events on workflow step nodes in the DAG visualization\n- Fetches step metadata from the workflow definition\n- Displays step information in a right-side drawer panel\n- Calls the content endpoint to load and display step content in a `<pre>` tag\n- Snippet:\n```javascript\nfetch('/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(projectLabel) + '/workflows/' + encodeURIComponent(workflowName) + '/steps/' + encodeURIComponent(stepName) + '/content')\n    .then(function(r) { if (r.ok) return r.text(); return ''; })\n    .then(function(text) {\n        var el = document.getElementById('drawer-content');\n        if (text) {\n            el.innerHTML = '<pre>' + text.replace(/&/g,'&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;') + '</pre>';\n        } else {\n            el.innerHTML = '<p style=\"color:var(--text-muted)\">No content available</p>';\n        }\n    });\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Workflow Visualization and Step Clicking**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 159-406)\n\n**Function:** `showWorkflow(wf)` - Renders an interactive DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) of the workflow\n- **SVG Generation:** Creates an SVG visualization with:\n  - Step nodes as rectangles with icons (agent, script, workflow icons)\n  - Edges showing workflow dependencies\n  - Terminal nodes (done/abort)\n  - Edge labels showing result values\n  - Merge patterns for multiple edges to same terminal\n\n**Step Node Creation (line 390):**\n```javascript\nsvg += '<g class=\"dag-node\" onclick=\"openDrawer(\\'' + wf.name + '\\',\\'' + s.name + '\\')\" style=\"cursor:pointer\">';\n```\n- Each step is clickable and calls `openDrawer()` with workflow name and step name\n- Creates a drawable panel showing step details\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Step Execution Output in Run Detail**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (lines 72-353)\n\n**Step Output Handler:** `handleAPIStepOutput` (lines 718-763)\n- **Endpoint:** `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n- **Purpose:** Fetches execution output for completed or running steps\n- **Features:**\n  - Optional filtering by log type (script, llm)\n  - Optional format parameter (raw vs parsed)\n  - Uses log index for fast lookup if available\n  - Falls back to captures store\n  - Parses Claude stream data if requested\n\n**UI Implementation:**\n- Steps displayed in an expandable table (accordion pattern)\n- Click on step row toggles the output panel\n- Output loads on demand via `fetch('/api/runs/' + runId + '/steps/' + step + '/output')`\n- Renders output in a styled `<pre>` tag with syntax highlighting\n- Preserves accordion state during polling updates\n\n**JavaScript Handler (lines 329-353):**\n```javascript\ndocument.addEventListener('click', function(e) {\n    var row = e.target.closest('.step-row');\n    if (!row) return;\n    var idx = row.dataset.index;\n    var outputRow = document.getElementById('output-' + idx);\n    // Toggle visibility and fetch content if needed\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Workflow Data API Endpoint**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1293-1411)\n\n**Handler:** `handleAPIWorkflows`\n- **Endpoint:** `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows`\n- **Returns JSON** with workflow definitions:\n  - Workflow name, location (container/host), file path\n  - Steps with type, results, and config\n  - Wires connecting steps with result labels\n  - Entry step name\n- **Parses** both container workflows (*.cloche files) and host.cloche\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Live Streaming and Polling**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n\n**Log Streaming (lines 114-159):**\n- **Endpoint:** `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` (Server-Sent Events)\n- Connects via EventSource for live log streaming\n- Parses JSON log lines: `{timestamp, type, content}`\n- Auto-scrolls log viewer to bottom\n- Closes when \"done\" event received\n\n**Handler:** `handleAPIStream` (lines 988-1085)\n- For active runs: subscribes to live broadcaster for real-time logs\n- For completed runs: streams archived full.log file\n- Supports log type parsing (LLM content extraction)\n\n**Steps Polling (lines 167-277):**\n- Polls `/api/runs/{id}` every 2 seconds for active runs\n- Updates step status and container state\n- Preserves accordion open/closed state\n- Re-fetches output for opened accordions with lazy loading\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Project Detail View - Step Drawer Panel**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 36-44)\n\n**Drawer HTML Structure:**\n```html\n<div class=\"drawer\" id=\"step-drawer\">\n    <div class=\"drawer-header\">\n        <span id=\"drawer-title\"></span>\n        <button class=\"drawer-close\" onclick=\"closeDrawer()\">&times;</button>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"drawer-body\" id=\"drawer-body\"></div>\n</div>\n```\n\n**CSS Styling:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (lines 498-555)\n- Fixed position right-side panel\n- Smooth slide-in animation (0.25s transition)\n- Scrollable content area\n- Responsive (full width on mobile)\n\n---\n\n### 8. **All API Endpoints for Step/Workflow Content**\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|\n| `/api/projects/{name}/workflows` | GET | List all workflows for a project |\n| `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` | GET | Get step definition content (prompt/script/command) |\n| `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` | GET | Get step execution output |\n| `/api/runs/{id}/stream` | GET | SSE stream of live logs |\n| `/api/runs/{id}` | GET | Get run details including step execution state |\n| `/api/projects/{name}/info` | GET | Get project info including prompt files |\n\n---\n\n### 9. **File Locations Summary**\n\n**Web Adapter Root:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/`\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - All HTTP handlers (60.5KB)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run execution view with step outputs\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Project view with workflow DAG and step drawer\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Runs list view\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` - Projects overview\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - Complete styling (615 lines)\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Content Flow Diagram**\n\n```\nUser clicks step in DAG visualization\n    ↓\nJavaScript: openDrawer(workflowName, stepName)\n    ↓\nFetch: GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\n    ↓\nHandler: handleAPIStepContent\n    - Parses workflow DSL\n    - Resolves file() references\n    - Reads prompt/script/command files\n    ↓\nReturns text/plain content\n    ↓\nRender in drawer panel <pre> tag with HTML escaping\n```\n\nFor step execution output:\n```\nUser clicks step row in run detail\n    ↓\nJavaScript: toggles accordion visibility\n    ↓\nFetch: GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output\n    ↓\nHandler: handleAPIStepOutput\n    - Queries log index or captures store\n    - Optional Claude stream parsing\n    ↓\nReturns text/plain output\n    ↓\nRender in accordion <pre> tag\n```"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a6a9b1f0a4ee6ed3d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51551\ntool_uses: 17\nduration_ms: 47273</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cb7499f-9015-41ef-ba66-388e58c4a9f5","uuid":"001ed0aa-78aa-4bad-9299-ffa1b9f543f8","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all web UI related code in this project. I need to understand:\n1. Where the web UI serves step content (the handler that returns step/workflow content)\n2. How steps are rendered in the UI (HTML/JS templates)\n3. How the content panel works when clicking on a workflow step\n\nLook for:\n- HTML templates with step content panels\n- Go handlers that serve step/script content\n- JavaScript that handles step clicks and content loading\n- Any API endpoints related to loading step content\n\nBe very thorough - check internal/adapters/ for web/http adapters, cmd/ for web servers, and any templates/ or static/ directories.","agentId":"a6a9b1f0a4ee6ed3d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Let me compile al