script files. I need to see what happens when it checks each field...\n\nTracing through the field checking...\n\nSo the bug is that `readScriptFromCommand` finds a compiled test binary named \"test\" in the project root and reads its entire contents as if it were a script. The fix needs to restrict file lookups to the `.cloche/scripts/` directory and validate that files are actually text, not binaries. I should also handle the case where `resolveFileRef` is given an explicit `file()` reference to a binary—that's a separate concern but worth noting.\n\nLooking at the task requirements more carefully, the rule is straightforward: only load content if the target is inside `.cloche/scripts/` AND is a text file. This check should apply to `readScriptFromCommand` and likely to `resolveFileRef` when handling the `run` config as well. I'm thinking through which other config fields might be affected—`prompt` should always be text and typically lives in `.cloche/prompts/`, while `command` is a string so it doesn't need this check.\n\nThe core fix should be in `readScriptFromCommand` to restrict file reads to `.cloche/scripts/` and verify the content is text rather than binary, then update the frontend to hide the content panel if nothing is returned. I'm seeing that the 'test' step is returning a 15KB response, which is likely the binary file content being pulled in. The issue is that `readScriptFromCommand` is reading files outside the allowed directories. I need to restrict it to only read from `.cloche/scripts/` or `.cloche/prompts/`, add a binary content check, and on the frontend hide the content panel entirely when there's nothing to display instead of showing a placeholder message.\n\nFor the `run` config with `file()` references, I should add a text file check there too since that's also pulling in content. Rather than modifying `resolveFileRef` globally which would affect all config types, I'll be more surgical: restrict `readScriptFromCommand` to `.cloche/scripts/`