es a script under `.cloche/scripts/`, that's worth loading and displaying. But for inline commands or references to files outside that directory, the command is already visible in the metadata, so loading content would either be redundant or potentially unsafe if it's binary. So the logic should be: load and show content only if it's a script under `.cloche/scripts/`, otherwise return 204.\n\nThat means I need to update a couple of the tests and also refine how `resolveFileRef` handles the `run` config to properly distinguish between these cases.\n\nChecking the path validation logic...\n\nI realize `readScriptFromCommand` doesn't currently enforce the `.cloche/scripts/` restriction, so I need to add that filter there as well to ensure only scripts from that directory are served.\n\nNow I'm mapping out all the changes needed: adding the `isTextContent` helper, updating `readScriptFromCommand` to validate both the directory and content type, adjusting the API handler to properly check file references, hiding the content panel in the frontend when there's nothing to display, and updating tests to cover the binary file scenario.\n\nLet me implement these changes...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3131,"cache_read_input_tokens":33089,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3131},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cb7499f-9015-41ef-ba66-388e58c4a9f5","uuid":"e5be43b1-9e30-4056-a501-0d88b0145074"}
