[2026-03-13T17:25:55Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E62eDBgf1b5dWsvwARzYAk","type":"tool_result","content":"   140→### Display\n   141→- Two-level tab navigation:\n   142→  - **Location tabs** (Container / Host) shown when both container and host workflows exist\n   143→  - **Workflow tabs** shown when the active location has multiple workflows\n   144→- Per workflow: a read-only DAG rendered client-side\n   145→  - Nodes = steps, rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon (agent 🤖 / script 📜 / workflow 🔁)\n   146→  - Edges = wires, labeled with the result name (e.g. `success`, `fail`)\n   147→  - Terminal nodes `done` and `abort` rendered distinctly\n   148→- Clicking a step node opens a right-side **drawer panel** (CSS slide-in):\n   149→  - Step name and type\n   150→  - Results list\n   151→  - `max_attempts` if set\n   152→  - For agent steps: full content of the referenced prompt file (loaded on demand)\n   153→  - For script steps: the `command`/`script` string or contents of the referenced script file\n   154→  - For host script steps: the `run` command string or contents of the referenced file\n   155→  - For workflow steps: displays the dispatched workflow name\n   156→  - Drawer closes via X button or Escape, returning focus to the DAG without page reload\n   157→\n   158→### DAG rendering\n   159→Client-side Sugiyama-style layered layout with no external library. Steps are assigned to\n   160→layers via longest-path from sources, then ordered within each layer using barycenter\n   161→heuristic (4 forward/backward passes) to minimize edge crossings. Layout flows\n   162→left-to-right with SVG Bezier curve edges.\n   163→\n   164→When multiple wires target the same terminal (`done` or `abort`), they merge into a\n   165→collector bus: individual curves from each source converge on a vertical dashed line,\n   166→which feeds a single arrow into the terminal node. This reduces wire clutter as graphs\n   167→grow in complexity.\n   168→\n   169→The DAG container scrolls horizontally when the graph exceeds the panel width.\n   170→\n   171→### API additions\n   172→\n   173→```\n   174→GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\n   175→```\n   176→\n   177→Response:\n   178→```json\n   179→[\n   180→  {\n   181→    \"name\": \"develop\",\n   182→    \"file\": \".cloche/develop.cloche\",\n   183→    \"location\": \"container\",\n   184→    \"steps\": [\n   185→      {\n   186→        \"name\": \"implement\",\n   187→        \"type\": \"agent\",\n   188→        \"results\": [\"success\", \"fail\"],\n   189→        \"config\": {\"prompt\": \".cloche/prompts/implement.md\", \"max_attempts\": null}\n   190→      },\n   191→      ...\n   192→    ],\n   193→    \"wires\": [\n   194→      {\"from\": \"implement\", \"result\": \"success\", \"to\": \"test\"},\n   195→      ...\n   196→    ],\n   197→    \"entry_step\": \"implement\"\n   198→  }\n   199→]\n   200→```\n   201→\n   202→The `location` field is either `\"container\"` or `\"host\"`. Host workflows are parsed from\n   203→`.cloche/host.cloche` and included in the same response.\n   204→\n   205→```\n   206→GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\n   207→```\n   208→\n   209→Returns the raw content of the prompt file or script for that step (plain text).\n   210→If the value is an inline command string (not a file reference), return it directly.\n   211→\n   212→## Template / file changes\n   213→\n   214→- New template: `templates/project_detail.html`\n   215→- New page registered in `NewHandler`: `\"project_detail\"`\n   216→- New routes registered in `NewHandler` mux\n   217→- Handler struct gains an optional orchestrator interface field (via `HandlerOption`)\n   218→\n   219→## Not in scope"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"baab609c-7354-4992-8237-78467d40b185","uuid":"ec2a8507-2e6a-478c-b181-08a8309b81f5","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md","content":"### Display\n- Two-level tab navigation:\n  - **Location tabs** (Container / Host) shown when both container and host workflows exist\n  - **Workflow tabs** shown when the active location has multiple workflows\n- Per workflow: a read-only DAG rendered client-side\n  - Nodes = steps, rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon (agent 🤖 / script 📜 / workflow 🔁)\n  - Edges = wires, labeled with the result name (e.g. `success`, `fail`)\n  - Terminal nodes `done` and `abort` rendered distinctly\n- Clicking a step node opens a right-side **drawer panel** (CSS slide-in):\n  - Step name and type\n  - Results list\n  - `max_attempts` if set\n  - For agent steps: full content of the referenced prompt file (loaded on demand)\n  - For script steps: the `command`/`script` string or contents of the referenced script file\n  - For host script steps: the `run` command string or contents of the referenced file\n  - For workflow steps: displays the dispatched workflow name\n  - Drawer closes via X button or Escape, returning focus to the DAG without page reload\n\n### DAG rendering\nClient-side Sugiyama-style layered layout with no external library. Steps are assigned to\nlayers via longest-path from sources, then ordered within each layer using barycenter\nheuristic (4 forward/backward passes) to minimize edge crossings. Layout flows\nleft-to-right with SVG Bezier curve edges.\n\nWhen multiple wires target the same terminal (`done` or `abort`), they merge into a\ncollector bus: individual curves from each source converge on a vertical dashed line,\nwhich feeds a single arrow into the terminal node. This reduces wire clutter as graphs\ngrow in complexity.\n\nThe DAG container scrolls horizontally when the graph exceeds the panel width.\n\n### API additions\n\n```\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\n```\n\nResponse:\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"develop\",\n    \"file\": \".cloche/develop.cloche\",\n    \"location\": \"container\",\n    \"steps\": [\n      {\n        \"name\": \"implement\",\n        \"type\": \"agent\",\n        \"results\": [\"success\", \"fail\"],\n        \"config\": {\"prompt\": \".cloche/prompts/implement.md\", \"max_attempts\": null}\n      },\n      ...\n    ],\n    \"wires\": [\n      {\"from\": \"implement\", \"result\": \"success\", \"to\": \"test\"},\n      ...\n    ],\n    \"entry_step\": \"implement\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\nThe `location` field is either `\"container\"` or `\"host\"`. Host workflows are parsed from\n`.cloche/host.cloche` and included in the same response.\n\n```\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\n```\n\nReturns the raw content of the prompt file or script for that step (plain text).\nIf the value is an inline command string (not a file reference), return it directly.\n\n## Template / file changes\n\n- New template: `templates/project_detail.html`\n- New page registered in `NewHandler`: `\"project_detail\"`\n- New routes registered in `NewHandler` mux\n- Handler struct gains an optional orchestrator interface field (via `HandlerOption`)\n\n## Not in scope","numLines":80,"startLine":140,"totalLines":224}}}
